<TITLE> Muslims observe Eid-e-Miladunnabi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 21 (bdnews24.com)Muslims in Bangladesh and elsewhere in the world observed holy Eid-e-Miladunnabi Friday amid befitting fervour and solemnity. On this 12th day of the Arabic lunar calendar month of Rabiul Awal in 570 AD, the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) was born in the Saudi Arabian city of Makkah. The Prophet died on another 12th Rabiul Awal, 63 years later. Various religious programmes, including processions, discussions, Quran recitation competition, exhibitions of religious books and seminars were organised in the city and elsewhere in the country. The Islamic Foundation took up elaborate programmes on the occasion starting Thursday night. Anjuman-e-Rahmania Mainia Maizbhandari brought out a procession in the morning. Anjuman-e-Asadia Nooriya Sehabiya also brought out another procession from Mirpur shrine. Main avenues in Dhaka were decorated with flags inscribed with 'Qalemaye Taiyaab', the national flag and colourful festoons. In separate messages, president Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed offered prayers for the well-being of the country, people and Muslim ummah. bd
